    "en": {
      "title": "15 deer died due to water aversion",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "During the examination carried out regarding the sudden death of some deer roaming in Homagama area within the last two days, it was revealed that the said deer died due to water aversion disease.",
        "The bodies of the dead deer were taken to the medical examination center for examination and it was found that the dead deer were suffering from anthrax, Director of Public Health Veterinary Service of the Ministry of Health, Dr. L.D. Kitsiri said.",
        "He said that 15 deer died in Homagama area on the 13th and 14th and after that the bodies of two deer were examined.",
        "He said that since it has been confirmed that there is distemper in Homagama area, the operation of injecting the dogs in that area and Colombo has been started."
      ],
